
// Concatenates the current value of [.pk] with the name of the node referenced by [.dp/#/*/name], separated by a comma, and assigns this concatenated string back to [.pk]. The [strings.concat] slot is used to merge these values, and [set-value] updates the [.pk] node with the result.
set-value:x:@.pk
   strings.concat
      get-value:x:@.pk
      get-value:x:@.dp/#/*/name
      .:,
